deck: A monster under the control of Mr. Gold, the main villain to Captain Canuck
description:
Character

Little is known about the creature called Oro. It first appears in Captain Canuck #4 - Aleph Part 4; Armed and Dangerous Part 2 and is shown following the direct orders of Mr. Gold

Powers & Abilities

The creature possesses gold colored flesh, no mouth or nose and it's physique is larger than that of the average man. It's left arm is a machine gun, which was used unsuccessfully on Captain Canuck but did successfully wound Kébec.

The creature would also later be revealed to be made up of a human toddler (though it is not specified exactly how the living liquid substance and the human interacted to create the living weapon Oro).

deck: Shuro Tsukasa was a woman who was a member of the popular music group GEsang. Like Aya Mikage, she also had Tennyo blood.
description:
Death

Shuro dies towards the end of Chapter 76, because her body rejects the drugs given to her by the Mikage Corporation. However, minutes before her death she goes on stage to perform her last concert—and while on stage reveals to the world that she is, in fact, a woman. Her fans are unfazed by her revelation, and lend her their spiritual support as Shuro prepares to sing her final song. In her last moments, she turns into her Tennyo form and uses her celestial powers to shatter the power-blocking bracelets that the Mikage corporation had placed on Aya and the other C-Genomers.
name: Shuro Tsukasa
